				<li id="16800765" class="cmnt-root" data="0" data-d="1669609608000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578193/Broadsword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">27 Nov 2022 23:26</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16800765" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">At base requirements, starting as Vagabond (so that is 14 STR, 13 DEX and 18 INT) the Carian Knight&apos;s Sword +10 has the highest AR (516AR)  out of the straight swords when infused with Magic. The closest is the Magic Broadsword +10 (510AR) with the Magic Lordsworn&apos;s Straight Sword +10 (495AR) taking the third place. So I don&apos;t really know what ya&apos;all are about in the comments about how the &quot;normal Longsword is just better&quot;. A odd little thing though is that the Carian Knight&apos;s Sword does less damage with the Ash of War than any other Straight Sword does, despite its higher AR. Likely due to its lower INT scaling than the rest.<br/><br/>Oh and if someone is wondering then this power difference remains the same at 60 STR and 60 INT, meaning the Carian Knight&apos;s Sword has the most AR in terms of Magic Damage Infusion. The same goes for the damage difference with the Ash of War. At 60 STR and 60 INT the Carian Knight Sword does 202 damage less on a fully charged Ash of War than every other Straight Sword with Magic Infusion. All other swords do the exact same amount of damage with the Ash of War.<br/><br/>To summarize that: <br/><br/>Carian Knight&apos;s Sword deals more damage per hit on R1/R2 attacks, but slightly less using the Ash of War (Carian Grandeur) than other Straight Swords. The upside is that it has a reliable trading tool when used correctly in its heavy attack.<br/></p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16800765" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16800765" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16800765"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16800765" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16800765"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
