				<li id="16680866" class="cmnt-root" data="5" data-d="1652408908000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578193/Broadsword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">12 May 2022 22:28</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16680866" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">If you particularly miss the movement you used to get out of the Broadsword in Dark Souls, I would recommend taking a look at the Warhawk&apos;s Talon! It&apos;s 1H and 2H uncharged R2 is a unique lunging double slash that covers more distance than the old Broadsword. Charging increases the distance you travel even further (and changes the 2nd R2 into another lunging double slash). I&apos;m constantly surprised by how much range I get, despite how short the blade is.<br/><br/>It is worth noting however that the damage and scaling is more comparable to the Short Sword, with a 10str/16dex requirement. The 1st uncharged R2&apos;s windup takes some getting used to, but the attack comes out very fast! Arguably safer than the Broadsword&apos;s R2 because you cover more ground much faster once you start moving. Personally I&apos;m having a lot more fun with the Talon&apos;s movement over the old Broadsword.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16680866" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16680866